claim: Vaccination with a higher-dose recombinant flu vaccine may induce a more robust antibody response than egg-based standard-dose vaccines.
explanation: A multi-column table listing trade names of various influenza vaccines (standard-dose egg-based IIV4, cell culture–based cIIV4, high-dose egg-based HD-IIV4, adjuvanted egg-based aIIV4, recombinant HA vaccine RIV4, and live attenuated egg-based LAIV4), their presentations, age indications, antigen content per virus per dose (µg HA or virus count), administration route, and mercury content. The table provides vaccine formulations and antigen dosages but contains no data on antibody responses or comparative immunogenicity, and thus does not support the claim. Note: No immunogenicity or antibody titer data are presented in the table.
